review_blob: Pours hazy orange with a mostly lasting thin off white head. Floral aroma, earthy, some toffee, lime. Taste is blood orange, spice, earthy, pine notes.
beer_name: To l Insane In The Grain

review_blob: Muted sweet malt initially. Richer bitterness than expected. Pilsner like bitterness on the finish...peppery. Lingers a bit.
Surprising light but fresh citrus/pine aroma. Tastes clean and citrusy, hints of pine, hints of caramel. Very well balanced and not overpowering. Clean and fresh and very nice and good.
Cloudy yellowish gold with a huge white head. Bottle pretty much exploded upon opening so probably only drank about a quarter of the bottle. Nice funk, cheese and citrus combo
Small white layer leaving. Dark brown color, quite light body. Aroma is barrel, sugar canes, raisins. Taste is sweet with chocolate, alcohol.

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Clear golden pour, with a white head. Tropical fruit, grapefruit, pine, pineapple, melon, moderately bitter, pithy, and mildly sweet.
beer_name: The Hop Concept Hll Melon & Blanc IPA

review_blob: soft orange, light off white head. Nose is funky Citrus rinds, a faint amount of biscuit malts. Lemons, funky but a little thin bodied. Drinkable
Pours a dark amber with small beige head that lasts. The aroma is bready malt and raisin. Thin mouth, toasted malt, dark fruit, light spice, sweet finish, good.
beer_name: To l Fuck Art - This is Advertising

review_blob: Clear amber colored with a small white head. Sweet and fruity aroma of caramel and marzipan. Sweet and fruity flavor of caramel and dried fruits with notes of marzipan.
The color is truly opaque. A brilliant complex, dark aroma. Just a touch too bitter for my taste on the finish, but that is emblematic of the American Stout style.
light citrus, rind, happy lemon, and brett .. . mouth is light and refreshing .. . this beer must do yoga, its very limber and calm- maybe too simple but a good brew

Heavy bodied and viscous with muted carbonation. Pours like used motor oil with a small coffee-colored head. Sweet coffee, roasted malt, good baking chocolate, raisin, smoke, tart plum. Strong sweet and bitter finish.
Tap @ Budapest. Gread redish color with white head. Nice aroma, caramel, candy, and some flower and citrus. Great.
Aroma is light citrus, light brett and some sweet bready pale malts. Bright pomelo character with some pithy bitterness, and a sweeter pale malt finish. The brett is not as strong in this one.
Clear yellow golden color, small white head. Smell and taste malts, lightly sweet grainyness, yeast, lightly bitter. Average body and carbonation.
Yellow hazy, white head. Aroma of fresh citrus, yeast, cilantro. Taste mild sweet citrus, cilantro notes. Almond. Fresh
The aroma holds tangerine, some dough bread, wheat, light peach and melon. Light sweet flavor with subtle funk, barnyard, tangerine, more peach. Light to medium bodied with average carbonation.

Pours clear dark golden with a small, staying, creamy white head. Aroma has pepper, coffee, malts, mild funk. Medium carbonation, fine dry and quite creamy mouthfeel. Flavour has good malty sweetness, caramel, coffee, lingering dryness.
Dark brown colour, beige foam, stays long. Aroma of caramel and dark fruit. Some banana. Bitter hoppy finish. Good and drinkable but I expected more.
2012 vintage. Dark brown pour with off white head. Aroma of prunes, caramel and raisins. Taste is semi sweet raisins, prunes and very slightly fruity, acetic notes.

2014 version. Aroma of fruits, citrus, wood, malt, lots of Brett funk, tart apples, some apricot, peach, hint of caramel, hoppy notes. Flavour is moderate to medium sour with a hint of hoppy bitterness in the finish. Very dry, body is medium.
Tap. So great color, and minimal head. Very good hungarian IPA from Roth Zoli. Love this!
Came from Bratislava, Slovakia. Pure amber color, with litthe white head. Nice citra aroma, freshness.
Aroma has citrus character, mango, light pineapple, honey. Taste has high earthy bitterness, light fruity notes, medium malty sweetness.
Tap @ Ganz Srz Budapest. Clear golden color with one finger head. Grassy and floral aroma. Grass, straw flavor with a dry finish. Nothing special, but a decent helles.
Colour is clear amber/gold. Aroma is malts, biscuit, caramel and toffee. Taste is the same as aroma with some honey and fruit notes. Light bitter finish. Medium carbonation

Bottle. Beige colored head. Sweet caramel and mild spices in the nose. Dark fruits, more residual sugars, caramel and mild banana bread flavors in the flavor. Sweet finish. Not much of a saison feel to it.
Bottle. Aroma is sweet malts, soured grapes, very light candy sugar, and light funk. Taste is very much the same with some tang and sour notes on the tip. Not too complex however.
Tap @ Wunder Budapest. Great very dark color. Very very nice dark lager!!!!
Semmikppen sem sr, de ha nem annak veszem nagyon rdekes, totlis kosz!! :)
Tap @ Budapest. Great strong cezh pilsner from this great brewery............
Tap. Classic rye ipa from Reketye. Nice color minimal head. Great...........
Tap @ Budapest. Brand new IPA from this great humgarian microbrewery with Equionox hops. nice!!
Tap. @ Budapest. Great weisbeer with some spice and vanilla. Perfect balance!!
Tap @ Budapest. Great irish red ale. Nice color, minimal head. not bad......
Tap @ Budapest. Nice smell and color. Drinkable irish red ale for the summer.
Tap @ Importer Budapest. Pours clear golden with a low head. Aroma is sweet malts with notes of camomile. Flavor is sweet malts, camomile and hops. Nice.
Tap @ Budapest Importer. Nothing so special, tipical vienna lager style beer. not bad.
Can @ Importer Budapest. Great session IPA. Easy, freshness, drinkable. perfect for the summer.
Bottle. Dark orange color, no head. Not bad, but too sweet for me, and the feeling like a candy...
Tap @ Budapest. Great APA with a lot of american hops. Nice again guys! cheers
Tap @ Hopfanatic Pub Budapest. Great orange color, minimal head. Nice and drinkable pale ale in Budapest.

Dark brown thin tan head. Aroma slight roasted toffe malts. Taste great dark malts toffee burnt toast dark fruits long bitter finish.
Clear golden pour, foamy white head. Aroma of grainy malts, soapy and some dishwasher. Flavor is soapy water with grains. Meh.
Bottle. Pours a dark golden color with a red tinge.......aroma of pine....taste is touch of earth, pine, wood, slight bitterness, finishing with a feint hint of alcohol.
Can. pale yellow coloured, white airy head, quite ordinary hop taste with some light herbal aroma
Bottle. Citric and wheaty notes in the aroma with coriander, mild yeast. Flavor is spice, oranges, wheat and yeast notes. Finish is lemony,
NBoppppee..... Aroma and taste of mass produced pilsener, not bad in that style.
Great brown color, minimal head. Toasted malt and chocolate aroma. Taste is sweet. Not for me.
